</para><quote depth="1"><quotepara depth="1">ld.so.1: /usr/local/bin/perl: fatal: libiconv.so.2: open failed: No
</quotepara></quote><para depth="0">                                       ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^
This would seem to indicate that your system is either missing some
needed library, or, perhaps more likely, it's in a non-standard place
that doesn't get found by ld when run from within procmail.  You might
want to check (if you have any add-ons to LD_LIBRARY_PATH) to see what
value (if any) it has when run from procmail.  By putting something like:

</para><para depth="0">NL="
"
LOG=${LD_LIBRARY_PATH}$NL

</para><para depth="0">in your .procmailrc

</para><quote depth="1"><quotepara depth="1">Anybody have any suggestions as to what's going on and how to fix
it?
</quotepara></quote><footer type="noise" depth="0">
